## Phase 1 — Conceptual Foundation and Core Architecture

Define the modular skeleton early: world-state vs simulation vs rendering vs input boundaries; a staged generation graph; an intent population pipeline; and the “safety invariants” (seed snapshots, dry-run validation, provenance) that must exist before complexity compounds.

### Seed tasks

- [ ] Define core abstractions and boundaries (world-state, sim, render, input, rules)
- [ ] Draft generation graph stages + interfaces (seed → terrain → biome → POI → entity → sim bootstrap)
- [ ] Specify intent resolver inputs/outputs (DM + player lore → systemic hooks)
- [ ] Establish safety invariants and provenance schema (snapshot/dry-run/traceability)

